üé≠ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì New Australian Play in London** üé≠

We are casting **four roles** for an exciting new Australian play, *The Beat of the Bronzewing*, which will have a **showcase reading at the Hen & Chickens Theatre, Islington, on November 12th**.

üå™Ô∏è **About the Play:**
When Peggy shows up at Lorraine‚Äôs shack in dead-end tropical Australia, she brings an irresistible offer: a one-way ticket out of there. But with a cyclone looming and old wounds resurfacing, can Lorraine be convinced she has nothing to lose?

‚ú® Longlisted for the **Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025**, *The Beat of the Bronzewing* explores the lives of three women in remote Australia, grappling with toxic femininity, domestic abuse, and rural isolation. Set against an evocative tropical landscape, the play is a gripping story of friendship, fear, and survival.

üë©‚Äçüé§ **The Team**
‚úçÔ∏è Writer & Producer: Charlotte Churcher
üé¨ Director: Chloe Cattin
ü§ù In partnership with the Australian Women‚Äôs Club London

üìÖ **Key Dates**
* **Auditions:** October 8th (12‚Äì5pm) at the Old Red Lion Theatre, Angel, Islington (alternative arrangements available if needed)
* **Rehearsals:** Sunday 9th November (10am‚Äì6pm) & Wednesday 12th November (from 2:30pm)
* **Showcase:** Tuesday 12th November at Hen & Chickens Theatre

üí∑ This is a **volunteer opportunity** with a ¬£50 contribution towards expenses.

üëâ To apply, please complete the form in full.
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSch7cgoIcL_f8KVARDySxKb7eM4Q2gpUXLmmDLPhppJCDDR-w/viewform

items.text:
This is for those who seek an intimate unique experience‚Ä¶

The Shop For Mortals and Fools
Opening soon in Central
london. Only for select customers.

Old relics, curious finds, hidden trinkets, and heirlooms ‚Äì treasures that whisper forgotten stories. In this enigmatic shop, a select audience is invited to an exclusive preview of its mysterious collection.

Inspired by Euripides‚Äô The Bacchae, this bold production delves into one of the greatest tragedies ever written, weaving an original and compelling narrative that explores power, vengeance. The production transforms a disused space into an atmospheric shop, a mythic world where gods, mortals, and unsuspecting customers collide in the voice of a woman.

Mystery awaits. Don‚Äôt miss out ‚Äì join the curious and fools, book your tickets today! https://www.tickettailor.com/events/theshopformortalsandallfools

And get this exclusive discount: F00ls100 or F00ls200

Co-Produced by Stanley Arts  photo with Kate Webster and photo by James Lawson Stanley ArtsKate WebsterJames Lawson@

items.summary:
This is for those who seek an intimate unique experience‚Ä¶

The Shop For Mortals and Fools
Opening soon in Central
london. Only for select customers.

Old relics, curious finds, hidden trinkets, and heirlooms ‚Äì treasures that whisper forgotten stories. In this enigmatic shop, a select audience is invited to an exclusive preview of its mysterious collection.

Inspired by Euripides‚Äô The Bacchae, this bold production delves into one of the greatest tragedies ever written, weaving an original and compelling narrative that explores power, vengeance. The production transforms a disused space into an atmospheric shop, a mythic world where gods, mortals, and unsuspecting customers collide in the voice of a woman.

Mystery awaits. Don‚Äôt miss out ‚Äì join the curious and fools, book your tickets today! https://www.tickettailor.com/events/theshopformortalsandallfools

And get this exclusive discount: F00ls100 or F00ls200

Co-Produced by Stanley Arts  photo with Kate Webster and photo by James Lawson Stanley ArtsKate WebsterJames Lawson@

sharedPost.text:
Hi Everyone, 

We are currently looking for freelance dance and drama artists (aged 18-30) based in and around Derbyshire to take part in a well-known musical theatre show! - Reveal happening soon!
 
Auditions will be free to attend, and the chosen cast will be given fair compensation for all rehearsals and performances. This opportunity is aiming to provide valuable experiences to those of you who are struggling to find a way into the industry.
 
Rehearsals will commence in February 2026 on Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays from 10am-3pm in Chinley (High Peak); and shows are currently set to take place on the 19th, 20th and 21st March 2026 at New Mills Art Theatre.
 
If you are interested in taking part and want to find out more information, please sign up to our mailing list below: https://forms.gle/5FJyLNDdafigtWRn9 
 

 
I am also on the lookout for local people that have experience being a light and/or sound operator. These roles will be paid ¬£14.50 per hour and will be needed for 40 hours between the 9th and 21st March. 
Potential to work full-time at New Mills Art Theatre after successful show.
 
Please email me at molly.sodenfreeth@act2.org.uk if you have any further questions.

Come along and join us at Ilkley Playhouse for this amazing event starting on September 25th and until 27th‚Ä¶
PS I‚Äôm directing one of the EIGHT short plays but don‚Äôt let that put you off :-)

items.text:
# CASTING CALL: JOIN OUR ACTING PODCAST

When a group of actors sit around a table and use their spoken words to portray characters all going on an adventure together, that's called a tabletop roleplaying game (TTRPG). Our gaming group plays a variety of tabletop roleplaying games and publishes the audio as a podcast. Example famous ttrpg podcasts: Critical Role, The Adventure Zone, etc. We react as our character to the scenario presented by the game master. We respond to challenges, overcome obstacles, make jokes and laugh with our fellow acting friends. Would you enjoy acting in-character for a podcast audience? Join us.

# When we play:

Weekends. Both European and American time zones. Joining us doesn't commit you to every weekend. Instead, we pick games we want to try and sign up for those calendar spots.

# How long we play / what it‚Äôs like:

Our members sit at their microphones for four hours talking their way through an adventure using their words and laughter to entertain each other. We use theater of the mind, saying out loud how far away targets are instead of looking at combat maps on a screen. The recordings are high quality, and we air the audio as a podcast. Don‚Äôt worry, we don‚Äôt publish our names or faces.

# System played:

We get to learn and play a different tabletop roleplaying game (ttrpg) system each session. There‚Äôs no financial burden to you. The systems are either free to everyone or we were sent a free promotional copy from its creator.

# Oneshot or campaign:

Both. Like a traditional campaign, we repeatedly meet familiar non player characters (NPCs), facing challenges and experiencing long term character growth. We play our same character for a year. Our characters start at low power in January, grow to epic max fighting strength by December, then retire. Like a oneshot, each individual episode opens with a beginning to its plot, and the exploration of its story ends after four hours.

# Game Mastering (GMing):

We rotate so that everyone is invited to be a player and a game master if they want. The GM gets to pick which ttrpg we play that weekend. If you find a fun ttrpg you want to try, you can sign up as the GM and be confident that there will be players excited to play with you. If you prefer to be a player every time that‚Äôs cool, too. Our members don't have to GM ever if they want a break from it. Getting to pick how often you GM really helps relieve burnout. GM as often as makes you happy.

# You can vibe check past games:

We're on itunes, spotify, youtube, and all the podcast apps. Our cast rotates. Skip around and listen to snippets from a few episodes to see which of our members you want to play with first. The episodes aren't all great, but we have fun together. This isn't a job. It's a hobby, a way to relax and laugh meeting new people who slowly over time become lifelong friends. It's okay to miss games; you aren‚Äôt expected to be present for every session. The opt-in format naturally minimizes table trouble because you can see who‚Äôs signed up to GM and play in a game before you join it, and can pick dates that have people you‚Äôre looking forward to playing with.

# Joining:

To join, email us at FirebreathingKittensPodcast at gmail dot com and tell us about your equipment. Our minimum requirement is 24 bit audio (not 16 bit). If you don‚Äôt know what 24 bit audio means that‚Äôs not a problem, the new members tab of FirebreathingKittensPodcast dot com has an equipment section that explains what all the microphone words mean with pictures and videos. We welcome members of all experience levels and will train you. The new members tab also has info about our format and answers to frequently asked questions. Minimum age 21 years old. We reply to all emails from people who have 24 bit audio within three days with a support agreement for you to sign, and then will guide you through character creation and train you how to record great audio.

topComments.text: The opt in schedule is the best part. Play when you're available, don't worry about when you're not.

**[PAID] Casting Call** ‚Äì Non-Featured Body Doubles+Stand In

Hi all! Pretty Much Films is casting for a Body Double for an upcoming online promo video shoot (30 Sept 2025).

Role Details: Body Double+Stand In

- Face will not be seen in the final video

- Only back, shoulders, and full body silhouette

- No acting experience required

Pay: SGD 150 per role

- Payment will be made after the shoot

Shoot Details

Usage: Non-featured, back-view only

Wardrobe: Provided by production

Roles

Body Double (Female)

1. Date/Time: 30 Sept 2025 (Overnight, approx. 5 hours)

2. Race: Chinese / Eurasian / Caucasian look

3. Height: ~155cm

4. Weight: ~52kg

5. Build: Lean or small/medium

To Apply

Please send the following to casting.prettymuch@gmail.com

With the subject

"BODY DOUBLE (Female) - (Your Name)"

1. Recent clear photos (within 2 months): Full body front & back

2. Full Recent Measurements (within 2 months)

- Mainly Height, weight, and shoe size

3. Availability on shoot dates

Please note: Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.

Thank you!

Wardrobe: Provided by production

Roles

Body Double (Female)

1. Date/Time: 30 Sept 2025 (Overnight, approx. 5 hours)

2. Race: Chinese / Eurasian / Caucasian look

3. Height: ~155cm

4. Weight: ~52kg

5. Build: Lean or small/medium

To Apply

Please send the following to casting.prettymuch@gmail.com

With the subject

"BODY DOUBLE (Female) - (Your Name)"

1. Recent clear photos (within 2 months): Full body front & back

2. Full Recent Measurements (within 2 months)

- Mainly Height, weight, and shoe size

3. Availability on shoot dates

Please note: Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.

Thank you!

items.text:
CASTING CALL

We‚Äôre looking for a female actor to join us this December for our RAPUNZEL pantomime (school tour). 

We‚Äôre casting either of the following parts, with our existing performer playing the opposite role. 

- Rapunzel (lead)
- Gothel (villain)

Last year was our best selling tour - but we hope to beat that this year! Because it‚Äôs schools, the shows are weekday mornings and early afternoons, so you‚Äôll have your evenings and weekends free. The performances are in the Norfolk, Suffolk and Cambridge area. 

We‚Äôre currently offering a minimum of ¬£870 - which will go up as we get more bookings in + travel expenses. 
The tour spans from 1st - 19th December 2025. 
Aiming to start weekly rehearsals asap - in Hunstanton (PE36). These are unpaid but we keep them as flexible as possible.

This will be our thirteenth panto tour, and we‚Äôve built up a good name in the area, with schools booking us year after year (even before we announce the title!) We pride ourselves on being a warm, friendly, but professional company.

If interested, please get in touch for further details - either by a PM on here, or via email - purple-dreams@hotmail.co.uk - I‚Äôm looking forward to hearing from (some of) you üôÇ

Many thanks
Tobias Nicholls
Creative Director 
Purple Dreams Productions

items.title: CASTING CALL

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

Looking for men 30-50ish to do short testimonial interview style ads over a zoom call. Roughly 1/2 hour of your time, pays $50. 

Interviews happen on Tuesdays at 230, 3, or 330 Tuesdays (PST/west coast time) so you must be available at that time. Also we need to have a quick phone call prior so I can make sure you can improvise/formulate sentences. 

If interested shoot me a dm! Thanks.

[PAID] *Repost*
Govt ad

1 main role, 5 feature role (main and feature do tvc and kv), 2 kv only talent 
- all need to be able to act naturally and follow directions, cant be stiff or awkward on camera

TVC filming date: 9th or 10th October, (1 day for main, 0.5 day for featured role)
KV filming date: 6th or 7th October, (0.5 day for main and featured and KV talent)
Loading: broadcast, social, digital, online - 12 months, Singapore only

(tvc + kv, 1.5 day total) Main role: Cleaner
Chinese male, 50s
self tape

- cleaning window with a smile (using squeegee on a pole, if have, if not can just use cloth and spray)
- sitting on chair, looking into camera pretending camera is employer, looking interested and nodding with a smile
- Outfit: button up collared short sleeve shirt with long pants (colour coordinate) , neat hair
     Rate:$1000(Total)

(tvc + kv, 2x 0.5 day total) Feature role #1: Employer
Malay Female, 40s
self tape:
- sitting down at desk and chopping documents + working on computer, pretend employee comes into office and she greets them with a smile, offering them a seat in front of the desk
- Outfit: formal office clothing (with blazer), neat hair and makeup
     Rate:$800(Total)

(tvc + kv, 2x 0.5 day total) Feature role #2: Kitchen Assistant
Indian female, late 30s
self tape:
- preparing something simple in the kitchen, smiling/enjoying her work
- Outfit: wearing apron and Long pants, hair tied up neatly and with light makeup
    Rate:$800(Total)

(tvc + kv, 2x 0.5 day total) Feature role #3: Admin staff (concierge)
Chinese female, 40s
self tape:
- working at the table on laptop, looking up to smile at customer and giving directions
- Outfit: formal, neat hair and makeup
     Rate:$800(Total)

(tvc + kv, 2x 0.5 day total) Feature role #4: Security Guard
Chinese male, 30s
Self tape:
- security guard walks around, inspecting area, turns and smiles and waves at a mall staff
- Outfit: black or daark blue polo/short sleeve shirt and pants, neat hair
     Rate:$800(Total)

(tvc + kv, 2x 0.5 day total) Feature role #5: Retail Assistant
Malay male, 20s
self tape:
- pretend to wheel a rack of clothes in a shop/arranging clothes, then turns to smile and wave at security guard
- Outfit: shirt and Long pants, neat hair 
     $800(Total)

(kv only talent, 1x 0.5 day total): Featured role #2 family members
Indian dad, late 30s-early 40s
Child, around 7-12 yo
- no need self tape, just picture only
     $600/Pax 

All Payment terms will be in 60 days 

If interested I will need your 

Name:
Age:
Height:
Role: 
Some recent pic
Only Singaporean/Pr May applys. Tks you

Only Shortlisted Talents will need to send in self tape

Ashley 
Whatapp:97679117
Ashley1981sg@gmail.com

**[PAID JOB]**

** **

**Project Overview** inclusive of photoshoot and video shoot (More details will be shared closer to the shoot date)
1. **Photoshoot:** Full-day session capturing talents in various spaces within the hotel
2. **Video shoot: **Half-day session featuring talents exploring the hotel

 

**Character Breakdown** 
* Age: 20s‚Äì30s 
* Look & Profile: Energetic and Vibrant

 

**Production Details** 
* Shoot Date: Late October ‚Äì Early November (tentative) ‚Äì 1.5 day shoot (final timing confirmed by 3 Oct)
* Location: Orchard, Central Region
* Usage/Loading: Perpetual loading for Social Media

 

**To apply**

Please send the following to** [jinying.yong@teamlewis.com** and** ericia.quek@teamlewis.com] by Friday, 26 September 2025**:

 
* Recent headshots
* Full body photos  
* Portfolio (if available) 
* Quotation/ Rate Cards 

 

Profile information:  
* Name  
* Age  
* Ethnicity  
* Height 
* Contact Number and Email Address  
* Instagram/Tiktok handles (if any) 

 

**Only shortlisted applicants will be notified. Thank you.**

I‚Äôm beyond excited to officially introduce One World Studios HQ ‚Äî a brand NEW multi-room creative content space in Baltimore, MD built for visionaries, storytellers, and creators of every kind.

Here‚Äôs what awaits you:

‚Ä¢ üé• All-White Photography & Video Room ‚Äì the perfect blank canvas.

Additional amenities include:

**üí° Wir bieten dir**
* **Mehrere feste Kurse pro Woche** ‚Äì mit Option auf Ausbau.

* Ein tolles Team, was dich mit offenen Armen empf√§ngt.
* Eine lebendige Tanz-Community und Auftrittsm√∂glichkeiten bei Events & Projekten.
* Raum f√ºr deine Kreativit√§t und Unterst√ºtzung bei der Umsetzung eigener Ideen.

**üìç Standort**

Zentrale Lage mit guter Erreichbarkeit (Leipzig, Halle, Jena, Weimar, Berlin, Frankfurt, Kassel, Hannover, G√∂ttingen, Coburg, Bamberg, N√ºrnberg).

Some songs just say it all ‚ù§Ô∏è
‚ÄúWith a Little Help from My Friends‚Äù is one of those a reminder that none of us get through life alone. Friends, family, supporters, and all of you who keep me going with your love for the music this one‚Äôs for you üôå

Be Grateful every day for the people who stand by you. üé∂

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

items.text:
The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of @arrowwooden next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8
The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

message.text:
üî• BULLET RUSH PREMIERE üî•

We‚Äôre at the Plaza Theatre putting the final touches on the Bullet Rush World Premiere ‚Äî and trust us, this is one night Atlanta will NEVER forget! üé¨‚ú®

From the red carpet lights to the heart-pounding action on screen, this premiere is pure adrenaline. Tickets are flying ‚Äî and once they‚Äôre gone, they‚Äôre gone!

üéü Don‚Äôt miss history in the making. Grab your tickets TODAY on Eventbrite or through the link in bio. October 19, 2025 is YOUR night to #FeelTheRush.

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/bullet-rush-movie-premiere-tickets-1684936322899?aff=oddtdtcreator

Awesome job to my brother

Evoque is looking for 2 male and 2 female dancers to join our amazing team at a luxury 5 Star hotel in Greece!

 Immediate start ‚Äì contract ends in October

 Food and accommodation included

 Work in a 5-star environment

 Incredible opportunity to perform and travel!

(Apply ASAP‚Äîpositions may fill quickly!)

How to apply:

 Email us at [evoquehub.com](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fevoquehub.com%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBEwblNXTEQweDZqeThqV05tNwEedL-NWDkIMZxb6cvvriVVbplNbRkFrPJkkt7YBX351mmiSYoHosuQ3Kxr8Xg_aem_GMwZV7LpxnP2iPUb2FGPJQ&h=AT2-0UHusi4vx5l3BUaILFHvnps5t1C0zJX2HqcVe2TaxLaFuCvQt9oq1DGIJqmmfZS7uLLRsg0Q4w5d6tql-PIhrPMCd86Ye-f06Eo1fVFzKwWDZh6LVf704r33Lc9b-Q8ewjHIcnUqf9pM-Q&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT2g4YR1RKDlmXE0DrbRBQGHIiA55XKWAznCE6gGapri1hn5eU5snihJX7TBnISpS8axFRpqTpETqTd8SxJja4nifItHqEmu8yxJYNLwYZoDb4pKkIG9xUkCNv8hhxaBZYGLoJV40DN6C5ps_XEMHfBXTXJs2IyyWczWKG7ND7SvGSZeyXxXTvZROcGf5FsOWe-OTRcoELzjD0SA5zh94A)

CEO

7:58 AM (2 hours ago)

to me

Dancer & singers job advertisement and schedule

 Last Summer Jobs ‚Äì Dance & Sing Entertainer Under the Greek Sun! 

(EU citizens & non-EU residents with a valid EU residence permit welcome)

This is your last chance to land a paid summer job in paradise!

Palmera Entertainment is hiring for the final dancer and singer positions at 5‚òÖ resorts in the beautiful Greek Islands.

If you love the stage, sun, and sea ‚Äì this job is for you.

 Available Roles for male & female 

            ‚Ä¢     Entertainer ( kids, Sports )

 ‚Ä¢ Dancer / performer 

 ‚Ä¢ Singer / Performer

 Location: 5‚òÖ Hotels ‚Äì Greek Islands

 Contract Dates: August 1st ‚Äì October 31st, 2025

 Swiss employment contract

 Net Salary: from ‚Ç¨800/month + commissions ( depends on positions& experiences)

 We Offer:

 ‚Ä¢  Free accommodation

 ‚Ä¢  Full board (3 meals/day) + drinks included in the main restaurant 

 ‚Ä¢  Free transfer from airport to hotel

 ‚Ä¢  Free internet & laundry service 

 ‚Ä¢  Free uniforms

 ‚Ä¢  Free rehearsals and show training

 ‚Ä¢  ‚Ç¨200 travel bonus (paid at contract end)

 ‚Ä¢  Full insurance (accident, pension, social)

 ‚Ä¢  Extra bonuses for merchandising promo

 ‚Ä¢  An unforgettable summer experience

 Typical Workday (~8 hrs):

 ‚Ä¢ Morning: 09:45‚Äì12:30 ‚Äì Activities or kids club

 ‚Ä¢ Afternoon: 14:45‚Äì17:00 ‚Äì Sports, games, or creative sessions

 ‚Ä¢ Evening: 20:00‚Äì23:00 ‚Äì Mini disco, shows, social dancing

 ‚Ä¢  5-6 performances/week, 1 hour per show

 ‚Ä¢  Mini Disco: 2‚Äì3 times/week (20:15‚Äì21:00)

 ‚Ä¢  Main Break: 17:00‚Äì20:00

 ‚Ä¢  Rehearsals: As needed (usually midday)

Schedules can vary slightly by hotel and concept ‚Äì flexibility is key.

topComments.text: Assuming you're about to sign with a legit agency, they might want you ro re-do these headshots in favour of more natural-looking ones, which offer more of a range. They might also ask you to consider a stage name, as there has already been a very successful actor with the same name as you.  They certainly won't want you taking unpaid work, and might also discourage taking very low-paid work. Chat to them, before accepting acting work. You're in a very over-saturated casting bracket, so you might find it advantageous long-term to keep training. Have you considered drama school?
Do you have a set of headshots?

items.text:
**URGENT CASTING CALL**

Student Short Film

**Shooting Date **- This Friday September 26th

**Location** - to be confirmed (in Edinburgh)

This is a student docu-drama about consciousness, and I am looking to film an Alien:Earth-style scene where a human conscious mind is being transferred onto an artificial being's. The part is only 60 seconds long.

**Roles Available:**

**Doctor - Female (30-ish)**

Supporting Role, a human individual asking interview-like questions to the artificial being to find out if she is human or not.

**MAIN ACTORS ALREADY FOUND**

As this is a student project it is non paid.

Contact me via email mathurin.aron@gmail.com or on WhatsApp 07394152555

Include name, age, headshot and any portfolio you possibly have and I will send you over the short script.

Looking forward to hearing from you and thank you so much already for reading this message!

This is a student docu-drama about consciousness, and I am looking to film an Alien:Earth-style scene where a human conscious mind is being transferred onto an artificial being's. The part is only 60 seconds long.

**Roles Available:**

**Doctor - Female (30-ish)**

Supporting Role, a human individual asking interview-like questions to the artificial being to find out if she is human or not.

**MAIN ACTORS ALREADY FOUND**

As this is a student project it is non paid.

Contact me via email mathurin.aron@gmail.com or on WhatsApp 07394152555

Include name, age, headshot and any portfolio you possibly have and I will send you over the short script.

Looking forward to hearing from you and thank you so much already for reading this message!

Casting Call ÌïúÍµ≠Ïù∏ Î∞∞Ïö∞Î•º Ï∞æÏäµÎãàÎã§

Location: Greater Vancouver Area
Production Type: Student / Non‚ÄëUnion
Format: Narrative short 
Shooting Date: November 13-15 2025 (3 consecutive days)
Compensation:  Catering, Crafty, imdb credit
Safety: Child-actor compliant set: guardian required on set for minor.
PRODUCTION COMPANY : Vancouver Film School

Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel (if applicable) to       Onlyforadaysf@gmail.com                  and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for. The selected actors will be sent sides with self-tape instructions.

Logline
A lonely Korean girl meets a magician hired to play her father for one day. A lie that becomes the most magical memory of her childhood.

Genre
Family Drama

Tone & Keywords
Warm, gently magical, grounded realism, themes of memory, identity, belonging, immigrant family, quiet humor.

ROLES
1) YUNSEUL / Ïú§Ïä¨ (Lead)
Female, 5-12, Korean. Sensitive, curious, and quietly lonely after moving to Canada. Hair‚Äëtwisting habit reveals anxiety. a believer who finds wonder in small things. The emotional heart of the film.
Language: English (primary), Korean (bonus).
Guardian: Parent/guardian required.

2) MAGICIAN (Lead)
Male, 25‚Äì35, Korean/Korean American. Witty on the surface, quietly lonely underneath. hides wounds behind jokes and tricks. A father‚Äëfor‚Äëa‚Äëday who is changed by Yunseul‚Äôs trust.
Language: English (primary), Korean (bonus).
Notes: Open to learning simple magic.

3) JUNGHEE / Ï†ïÌù¨ (Lead)
Female, 25‚Äì35, Korean/Korean‚Äëdescent. Protective, practical, and loving; carries guilt over the story she tells her daughter about the absent father. Hires the Magician out of fierce love and hope.
Language: English (primary), Korean (bonus).

4) CHUY (Supporting)
Male, 25‚Äì35, Korean/Korean‚Äëdescent. Playful ‚Äúuncle‚Äù energy, eases the mood with quick humor. Quietly honest protects the boundary of magic so it keeps its power.
Language: English (primary).
